{"parse":{"title":"diet","pageid":44581,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Diet|diệt|diët|DIET}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|diët||dated|rare}}\n* {{alt|en|diate||obsolete}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdaɪət/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-diet.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdaɪət/|/ˈdiːət/}} {{q|deliberative assembly}}\n* {{rhymes|en|aɪət|iːət|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|diet}}, {{m|enm|dyet}}, {{m|enm|diete}}, from {{der|en|fro|diete}}, from {{der|en|la-med|dieta||regimen, regulation; assembly}}, from {{der|en|la|diaeta}}, from {{der|en|grc|δίαιτα}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|food a person or animal consumes}}The [[food]] and [[beverage]] a person or animal consumes.\n#: {{ux|en|The '''diet''' of the giant panda consists mainly of bamboo.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2013|author=Martin D Buckland; Lynda Hall; Alan Mowlem|title=A Guide to Laboratory Animal Technology|page=56\n|passage=It is common policy to order no more '''diet''' than will be used within one month.}}\n# {{senseid|en|controlled regimen of food and drink choices}} {{lb|en|countable}} A [[controlled]] [[regimen]] of food and drink choices, as to gain or lose [[weight]] or otherwise influence [[health]].\n#: {{ux|en|He's been on a '''diet''' since he found out that he has coronary atherosclerosis.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The doctor put me on a low-salt '''diet'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|My  jeans are too tight, so I'm going on a '''diet'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|by extension}} Any habitual [[intake]] or [[consumption]].\n#: {{ux|en|He's been reading a steady '''diet''' of nonfiction for the last several years.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Farhad Manjoo|title=Can We Please Stop Talking About Stocks, Please?|work=The New York Times|date=2021-02-03|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/03/opinion/gamestop-stock-market-economy.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Last week the aging video game retailer emerged as the hottest stock on Wall Street, a story just unexpected and absurd enough to fill the new Trump-shaped void in our nation’s media '''diet'''.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|antidiet|Diet Coke|dietic|dietitian|dietless|dietology|dietwise|diety|misdiet|nondiet|palaeodiet|paleodiet|prediet|superdiet|Atlantic diet|carnivore diet|lion diet|Stone Age diet|hypoglycemic diet|keto diet|ketogenic diet\n|dietarian\n|dietary\n|dietary fiber|diet culture\n|dieter\n|dietetics|Paleo diet\n|5:2 diet\n|don't diet, try it\n|Atkins diet\n|balanced diet\n|crash diet|road diet\n|desert the diet|Western pattern diet\n|elimination diet|South Beach Diet\n|fad diet\n|liquid diet\n|Maduro diet|Stillman diet\n|Mediterranean diet\n|mono diet\n|Okinawa diet\n|Zone diet}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en\n|dieting#Noun<pos:n>\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|ja|ダイエット|bor=1}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|food a person or animal consumes}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|dieet}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|dietë|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|حِمْيَة|f}}, {{t|ar|حِمْيَة غِذَائِيَّة|f|tr=ḥimya ḡiḏāʔiyya}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|սննդակարգ}}, {{t+|hy|դիետա}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|pəhriz}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|дые́та|f}}, {{t|be|е́жа|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|дие́та|f}}, {{t+|bg|хра́на|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|dieta|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|飲食|tr=yǐnshí}}, {{t+|cmn|吃喝|tr=chīhē}}, {{t+|cmn|食物|tr=shíwù}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|strava|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|kost|c}}, {{t|da|ernæring|c}}, {{t+|da|næring|c}}, {{t+|da|føde|c}} {{qualifier|animal}}, {{t+|da|kost|c}}, {{t+|da|føde|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|dieet|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ruokavalio}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|diète|f}}, {{t+|fr|régime|m}}\n*: Middle French: {{t|frm|diete|f}}\n*: Old French: {{t|fro|diete|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|dieta|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Ernährung|f}}, {{t+|de|Nahrung|f}}, {{t+|de|Speiseplan|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|διατροφή|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|διαίτημα|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|דִּיאֵטָה|f|tr=diéta}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|táplálék}}, {{t+|hu|étrend}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|mataræði|n}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|dieta}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|aiste bia|f}}, {{t|ga|réim bia|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|dieta|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|飲食|tr=いんしょく, inshoku}}, {{t+|ja|ダイエット|tr=daietto}}\n* Javanese: {{t|jv|diet}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|емдәм}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|[[របប]][[អាហារ]]|tr=rɔbɑɑp ʼaahaa}}, {{t+|km|អាហារ}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|식단(食單)}}, {{t+|ko|다이어트}}\n* Lao: {{t+|lo|ອາຫານ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|victus|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|и́схрана|f}}, {{t|mk|дие́та|f}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|whiringa kai}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|diett|m}}, {{t+|nb|ernæring|m|f}}, {{t|nb|næring|m|f}}, {{t|nb|kosthold|n}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|dièta|f}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|رِژیم}}, {{t|fa-ira|رِژیمِ غِذایی}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|dieta|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|dieta|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|рацио́н|f}}, {{t+|ru|дие́та|f}}, {{t+|ru|пита́ние|n}}, {{t+|ru|пи́ща|f}}, {{t+|ru|стол|m}}, {{t+|ru|еда́|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|и̏схрана|f}}, {{t|sh|хра́на|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|ȉshrana|f}}, {{t+|sh|hrána|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|strava|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|prehrana|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|dieta|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|kost|c}} {{qualifier|human}}, {{t+|sv|föda|c}} {{qualifier|animal}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|உணவு}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|ఆహారం}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|อาหาร}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|diyet}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|پرهیزانه|tr=perhizane}}\n* Turkmen: {{t+|tk|berhiz}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|діє́та|f}}, {{t+|uk|ї́жа|f}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|chế độ ăn uống}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|controlled regimen of food}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|dieet}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|dietë|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|حِمْيَة|f}}, {{t|ar|نِظَام غِذَائِيّ|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|ريجيم|m|tr=rījīm}}, {{t|arz|ريچيم|m|tr=rījīm}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{t|afb|رجيم|m|tr=rijīm}}, {{t|afb|دايت|m|tr=dāyt}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|رَجيم|m|tr=rajīm}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|սննդակարգ}}, {{t+|hy|դիետա}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|pəhriz}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|дые́та|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|дие́та|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|dieta|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|節食|tr=jiéshí}}, {{t+|cmn|飲食療養|tr=yǐnshí liáoyǎng}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|dieta|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|kur|c}}, {{t|da|diæt|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|dieet|n}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|dieet}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|dieetti}}, {{t+|fi|ruokavalio}} {{qualifier|general}}, {{t+|fi|laihdutuskuuri}} {{qualifier|for losing weight}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|régime|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|dieta|f}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|დიეტა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Diät|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|δίαιτα|f}}, {{t+|el|διαιτολόγιο|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|דִּיאֵטָה|f|tr=diéta}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|आहार|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|étrend}}, {{q|refraining from certain foods, especially at bowel complaints}} {{t+|hu|diéta}}, {{q|slimming diet}} {{t+|hu|fogyókúra}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|dieto}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|dieta}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|réim|f}}, {{t|ga|réim bia|f}}, {{t|ga|aiste bia|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|dieta|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|ダイエット|tr=daietto}}\n* Kashubian: {{t|csb|dieta|f}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|емдәм}}, {{t|kk|диета}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|다이어트}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|پارێز}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|диета}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|diaeta|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|diēta|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|dieta|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|дие́та|f}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|mahere kai}}, {{t|mi|mahere kai hauora}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|पथ्य|f}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|رِژیم}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|dieta|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|dieta|f}}, {{t+|pt|regime|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|dietă|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|дие́та|f}}, {{t|ru|[[режи́м]] [[питание|пита́ния]]|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|дије́та|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|dijéta|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|diéta|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|dieta|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|dieta|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|bantning}}, {{t+|sv|diet|c}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|парҳез}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|உணவு}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|diyet}}, {{t+|tr|rejim}}, {{t+|tr|perhiz}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|پرهیز|tr=perhiz}}, {{t|ota|یمكدن صاقنمه|tr=yemekden sakınma}}, {{t|ota|قورنمه|tr=kurunma}}, {{t|ota| حمیه|tr=himye}}\n* Turkmen: {{t+|tk|berhiz}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|diyeta}}, {{t+|uz|parhez}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|chế độ ăn kiêng}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|habitual consumption}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|дие́та|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t-needed|cmn}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kulutus}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Kost|f}}, {{t+|de|Konsum|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|δίαιτα|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|dieta|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|дие́та|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|dieta|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|дие́та|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|дије́та|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|dijéta|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|of a [[food]] or [[beverage]]}} Containing less fat, salt, sugar, or calories than normal, or claimed to have such.\n#: '''''diet''' soda''\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1982|author=Consumer Guide|title=Dieter's Complete Guide to Calories, Carbohydrates, Sodiums, Fats & Cholesterol|page=18|passage=Many grocery chains offer premium-priced lean or '''diet''' hamburger; but the fat content is usually at least 10 percent, sometimes 15 percent or more.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1998|author=Andy Sae|title=Chemical Magic from the Grocery Store\n|passage=The difference in weight (mass) of the regular and the '''diet''' drink of the same brand roughly equals to the amount of sugar in the regular drink.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2010|title=Lonely Planet Peru|page=347|isbn=1742203698\n|passage='''Diet Light''' (Pizarro 724; snacks S2-7; 9:30am-10pm)<br/>This perennially busy place serves not-very-'''diet''', but yummy nonetheless, ice cream (S2 to S5) and whopping servings of mixed fruit (S3) – with ice cream.}}\n#* {{see more citations|en}}\n# {{lb|en|informal|figurative}} Having certain traits subtracted.\n#: {{synonyms|en|lite}}\n#: {{ux|en|You folks reduce it to the bible only as being authoritative, impoverishing the faith. \"Christianity Lite\", '''diet''' Christianity for those who can't handle the Whole Meal.}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|containing lower-than-normal amounts of calories}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t-needed|cmn}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|vähäkalorinen}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|diétás}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|diet}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|диети́ческий}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|dieten}}, {{m|enm|dyeten}}, {{m|enm|diȝeten}}, from {{der|en|fro|dïeter}} and {{der|en|la-med|diētāre}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To modify one's food and beverage intake so as to decrease or increase body weight or influence [[health]].\n#: {{ux|en|I've been '''dieting''' for six months, and I've lost some weight.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|dated}} To regulate the [[food]] of (someone); to put on a diet.\n#* {{RQ:Burton Melancholy|edition=2nd}}<!--, I.iii.1.2:-->\n#*: they will '''diet''' themselves, feed and live alone.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1887|title=Medical Press and Circular|volume=94|page=461\n|passage=When all signs of effusion, dulness, pain, &oelig;gophony, and cough had disappeared he was '''dieted''', stimulated, and tonicked.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1920|author=w:Edward Carpenter|title=Pagan and Christian Creeds|year_published=1921|location=New York|publisher=Harcourt, Brace and Co.|page=45|passage=As illustrating the belief that the Baptism by Blood was accompanied by a real regeneration of the devotee, Frazer quotes an ancient writer who says that for some time after the ceremony the fiction of a new birth was kept up by '''dieting''' the devotee on ''milk'', like a new-born babe.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} To [[eat]]; to take one's meals.\n#* {{RQ:Bacon Essayes|chapter=Of Travel|passage=Let him{{...}}'''diet''' in such places, where there is good company of the nation, where he travelleth.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|transitive}} To cause to take food; to [[feed]].\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Othello|text=But partly led to '''diet''' my revenge&nbsp;{{…}}.}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to regulate the food of someone}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|slanke}}, {{t|da|sætte på diæt}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ruokkia}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|diétára fog}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|estar a dieta}}, {{t|es|estar dietado}}, {{t|es|estar adietado}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|banta}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|diyete sokmak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to modify one's food and beverage intake}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|slanke}}, {{t|da|være på diæt}}, {{t|da|være på slankekur}} {{qualifier|to lose weight}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[noudattaa]] [[ruokavaliota]]}}; {{t+|fi|laihduttaa}} {{qualifier|specifically with the aim of reducing one's weight}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|diétázik}}, {{q|to lose one's weight}} {{t+|hu|fogyókúrázik}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|whakatiki}} {{qualifier|to reduce weight}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|poner a dieta}}, {{t+|es|dietar}}, {{t+|es|adietar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|banta}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|diyet yapmak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to take one's meals}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ruokailla}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to cause to take food; to feed}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|syöttää}}, {{t+|fi|ruokkia}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|diet}}, {{m|enm|dyet}}, from {{der|en|fro|diete}}, from {{der|en|la-med|diēta}}, {{m|la|diaeta|t=a public assembly; set day of trial; a day's journey}}, from {{der|en|grc|δῐ́αιτα||way of living, living space; decision, judgement}}, influenced by {{der|en|la|diēs|t=day}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{sid|en|Q2282872}} {{lb|en|usually capitalized as a proper noun}} A [[council]] or [[assembly]] of leaders; a formal deliberative assembly.\n#: {{alti|en|Diet<id:Q2282872>}}\n#: {{coi|en|the National '''Diet''' of Japan}}\n#: {{ux|en|They were given representation in some important '''diet''' committees.}}\n# {{lb|en|Scotland}} A session of exams.\n#* {{quote-web|en|title=Coronavirus: School exam timetable could be put back next year|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-53040593|work=BBC News website|publisher=BBC|date=14 Jun 20|accessdate=23 April 2026|text=Normally the '''diet''' begins towards the end of April.}}\n# {{lb|en|Scots law}} A [[criminal]] [[proceeding]] in [[court]].\n# {{lb|en|Scotland}} A [[clerical]] or [[ecclesiastical]] [[function]] in Scotland.\n#: {{coi|en|a '''diet''' of worship}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|Dietman\n|National Diet\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|council of leaders}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|بَرْلَمَان|m}}, {{t|ar|مَجْلِس|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|議會|tr=yìhuì}}, {{t+|cmn|國會|tr=guóhuì}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|parlament|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|parlement|n}}, {{t+|nl|rijksdag|m}}, {{t+|nl|landdag|m}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|valtiopäivät|p}}\n* French: {{qualifier|Diet of Japan}} {{t+|fr|Diète|f}}, {{t+|fr|parlement|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Versammlung|f}}, {{t+|de|Parlament|n}}, {{qualifier|Diet of Japan}} {{t|de|Kokkai|n}}, {{t+|de|Tag|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|δίαιτα|f}}, {{t+|el|συνέλευση|f}}, {{t+|el|σύνοδος|f}}, {{t+|el|βουλή|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|דִּיאֶט|m|tr=díet}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|országgyűlés}}, {{t+|hu|parlament}}, {{q|archaic in this sense}} {{t+|hu|diéta}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|dieto}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|dieta|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|議会|tr=ぎかい, gikai}}, {{t+|ja|国会|tr=こっかい, kokkai}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|собрание|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|dieta|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|парла́мент|m}}, {{qualifier|Diet of Japan}} {{t|ru|кокка́й|m}}, {{t+|ru|сейм|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|dag|c}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|diyet}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=deit|-tide|dite|edit|edit.|tide|tied}}\n\n{{C|en|Government|Nutrition}}\n\n==Basque==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{eu-pr}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{eu-verb form|izan<nor-nori-nork>}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nRevival by Flemish nationalists of {{der|nl|dum|diet||people, folk}}, from {{der|nl|gmw-pro|*þeudu}}, from {{der|nl|gem-pro|*þeudō}}, from {{der|nl|ine-pro|*tewtéh₂}}. Compare {{m|nl|Diets||Dutch, German}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/dit/}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|diet}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|it}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|n|-|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|archaic}} [[folk]], [[people]]\n# {{lb|nl|Belgium|archaic}} the combined [[Flemish]], [[Dutch]] and [[Afrikaner]] [[people]]\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|nl|diedenweg}}, {{l|nl|diets maken}}\n* {{l|nl|Diets}}, {{l|nl|Dietsland}}, {{l|nl|Platdiets}}\n* {{l|nl|beduiden}}, {{l|nl|duiden}}, {{l|nl|duidelijk}}, {{l|nl|verduidelijken}}\n* {{l|nl|Duits}}, {{l|nl|Duitsland}}, {{l|nl|Nederduits}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n{{wp|id:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{internationalism|id}}, {{bor+|id|nl|dieet|diet|nocap=1}}, from {{der|id|dum|diete}}, from {{der|id|fro|diete}}, from {{der|id|la-med|dieta||regimen, regulation; assembly}}, from {{der|id|la|diaeta}}, from {{der|id|grc|δίαιτα}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{id-pr|diét}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun|head=diét}}\n\n# {{l|en|diet}}\n#: {{syn|id|ms:pemakanan}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{id-verb|head=diét}}\n\n# to {{l|en|diet}}\n#: {{syn|id|berdiet<q:chiefly formal>}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|id\n|berdiet<t:to diet>\n|pediet<t:dieter>\n|pendiet<t:dieter>\n}}\n{{col|id\n| diet aterogenik| diet Atkins| diet bebas jerawat| diet dadakan| diet detoks| diet dukan| diet elemental| diet eliminasi| diet GM| diet Hay| diet kapas| diet karbo| diet karbohidrat rendah| diet keto| diet ketogenik| diet kombinasi| diet lengkap| diet makanan mentah| diet makrobiotik| diet mediterania| diet mono| diet monotrofik| diet murni| diet paleo| diet panjang umur| diet pemulihan| diet praktis| diet puasa berjeda| diet rendah garam| diet rendah kolesterol| diet semimurni| diet suplemen| diet tiga jam| diet yoyo\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Jamaican Creole==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{der+|jam|en|date}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{jam-noun}}\n\n# [[date]]\n\n==Latvian==\n\n===Verb===\n{{lv-verb||1st|dej|dej||dej}}\n\n# to [[dance]] {{lb|lv|archaic}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{lv-conj|die|dej|1st|dej||dej||spal}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* [[dejot]]\n* [[dancot]]\n* [[griezt danci]]\n* [[pamest līku kāju]]\n\n==Middle Dutch==\n\n===Contraction===\n{{head|dum|contraction}}\n\n# {{contraction of|dum|die|dat}}\n# {{contraction of|dum|die|het}}\n\n==Middle Irish==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|mga|la-med|diēta||daily allowance, regulation, daily order}}, from {{der|mga|grc|δίαιτα}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{mga-noun|f}}\n\n# [[#English|diet]], [[régime]]; [[dieting]]\n\n===Mutation===\n{{mga-mutation|d|iet}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DIL|16242}}\n\n==Northern Sami==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|se|smi-pro|*tietë}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{se-IPA}}\n\n===Determiner===\n{{head|se|determiner|cat2=demonstrative determiners}}\n\n# [[that]] (near the listener)\n\n====Inflection====\n{{se-infl-dem|diet}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{R:Álgu|21675}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|nb|dia}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|nb|verbf}}\n\n# {{infl of|nb|die||sim|past|and|past|part}}\n\n==Old English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ang-IPA|dīet}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|ang|verb form|head=dīet}}\n\n# {{infl of|ang|dīedan||3|s|pres|indc}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|diet}}. {{doublet|pt|dieta}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|br=dáite,dáiete,dáiet<q:careful pronunciation>}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{pt-adj|inv=1}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|of [[food]] or [[beverage]]}} {{l|en|diet}} {{gloss|containing lower-than-normal amounts of calories}}\n#: {{syn|pt|dietético}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|pt|light}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|sv|fro|diete}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# a {{l|en|diet}}\n#: {{ux|sv|gå på en '''diet'''|be on a '''diet'''}}\n#: {{ux|sv|leva på en '''diet''' av potatis och öl|live on a '''diet''' of potatoes and beer}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-er}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|sv|5:2-diet}}\n* {{l|sv|dietist}}\n* {{l|sv|dietspecialist}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|sv|banta}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|sv|a=deit|Edit}}\n\n==Zhuang==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|za|zh|-}} {{ltc-l|鐵}}. {{doublet|za|lek|lik}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{za-pron}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{za-head|noun}}\n\n# [[iron]] {{gl|metal}}\n#: {{syn|za|lek|lik|faz|q1=dialectal|q2=dialectal|q3=dialectal}}\n\n{{C|za|Metals}}"}}